(x-y)f(x+y) -(x+y)f(x-y) =4xy(x^2-y^2)
(x-y)f(x+y) -(x+y)f(x-y) =4xy(x-y)(x+y)
\Rightarrow \frac{(x-y)f(x+y)}{(x-y)(x+y)} -\frac{(x+y)f(x-y)}{(x-y)(x+y)} =4xy
\Rightarrow \frac{f(x+y)}{x+y} -\frac{f(x-y)}{x-y} =4xy
(x+y)^2 -(x-y)^2 = 4xy
\Rightarrow \frac{f(x+y)}{x+y} =(x+y)^2
\frac{f(x-y)}{x-y} =  (x-y)^2
\frac{f(x)}{x} =x^2
\Rightarrow f(x) =x^3
f(x) =x^3 +kx
\Rightarrow \frac{f(x+y)}{x+y} -\frac{f(x-y)}{x-y} =4xy=(x+y)^2-(x-y)^2
\frac{f(x+y)}{x+y}-(x+y)^2=\frac{f(x-y)}{x-y}-(x-y)^2
x\to \frac{x+y}{2}
y \to \frac{x-y}{2}
\frac{f(x)}{x}-(x)^2=\frac{f(y)}{y}-(y)^2=k(say)
f(x)=x^3+kx
(x-y)k(x+y)-(x+y)k(x-y)=0
k
